###
How can you find out what Ubuntu package provides `libruby.so`?
===
```
# dpkg -S libruby
libruby2.5:amd64: /usr/share/systemtap/tapset/libruby2.5-x86_64-linux-gnu.stp
libruby2.5:amd64: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libruby-2.5.so.2.5
libruby2.5:amd64: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libruby-2.5.so.2.5.1
libruby2.5:amd64: /usr/share/doc/libruby2.5/copyright
libruby2.5:amd64: /usr/share/doc/libruby2.5
libruby2.5:amd64: /usr/share/lintian/overrides/libruby2.5
ruby2.5-dev:amd64: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libruby-2.5.so
libruby2.5:amd64: /usr/share/doc/libruby2.5/changelog.Debian.gz
```
